nodes.documentation:
# VOTE INTEGER SIZE DECISIONS
This governance contract has a number of optimizations built specifically for 
the Exim blockchain.  These optimizations are based on:
1. Quadratic voting system where voting v costs v**2 tokens
2. A total token supply for 150M tokens
3. Minimum requirement of 500 tokens to cast vote
This leads to:
- MAX SINGLE VOTE (uint16): Maximum vote is sqrt(150M)=12,247. Each 
BallotRecord stores the vote as a uint16, which handles up to 65,536.
- MAX TOTAL VOTE (int24): Atleast one person needs to be nominated by a voter, that voter 
must hold 500 tokens and casts 32 votes (for 1024 tokens)for the nomination leaving: 
150M - 500 - 1024 = 149998476 tokens in circulation. Each voter thereafter must also hold 500 tokens 
and can cast a minimum of 1 vote with 1 token.  and  so at a max supply of 149998476, the max number 
of votes any candidate can receive in an election is 32 + 149998476/501=299k votes, either positive or 
negative. The nominee and governance ballots store this in the smallest 
possible int, int24 (maxes at +/-8.35M).
- MAX AMOUNT (uint32): If somebody held every token and used every one to vote, 
the amount for that vote would be 150M.  The BallotRecord and NomineeBallot 
store the amount as a uint32, the smallest uint which can hold 150M (maxes at 4.29B).
